1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:04,600
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:06,167 --> 00:00:07,733
I want to dance with you.

3
00:00:07,867 --> 00:00:09,400
You know I can't dance.

4
00:00:09,533 --> 00:00:11,533
- Really?
- Oh, no!

5
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:13,533
Ash, my child,
I just want you to know

6
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:16,000
that dad loves you
very, very much.

7
00:00:16,133 --> 00:00:18,367
I will never get tired
of dancing with you

8
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:19,700
whenever you want.

9
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,167
Your biggest mistake?

10
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,867
So that's all I ever was
to you, Edward.

11
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,633
I was just a replacement to you!

12
00:00:24,767 --> 00:00:26,100
That's why I broke up with you.

13
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:29,333
Leaving you was
the best decision

14
00:00:29,467 --> 00:00:31,800
that I've made in my whole life.

15
00:00:31,933 --> 00:00:33,200
I hate you!

16
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:38,300
You are the reason for all
the misfortune in my life!

17
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:39,833
Why did you do that?

18
00:00:39,967 --> 00:00:40,867
Did you want to kill me?

19
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,767
Edward...

20
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:44,133
[PHONE RINGING]

21
00:00:44,267 --> 00:00:46,933
- Hello, Edward?
- Marj, help me!

22
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,467
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

23
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:57,967
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

24
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:11,600
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

25
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:22,067
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

26
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,000
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

27
00:01:33,133 --> 00:01:37,133
- 1, 2, 3, 4...
- 1, 2, 3, 4...

28
00:01:37,267 --> 00:01:38,200
[CHUCKLES]

29
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:41,200
- 5, 6, and then, 7...
- 5, 6...

30
00:01:41,367 --> 00:01:42,233
Hey!

31
00:01:42,367 --> 00:01:44,300
[UPBEAT MUSIC CONTINUES]

32
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:50,633
How do you do that?

33
00:01:54,133 --> 00:01:56,167
Dad? Dad, what are you doing?

34
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:03,767
I want to dance with you.

35
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:04,933
What?

36
00:02:05,067 --> 00:02:06,867
You know I can't dance.

37
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,367
Really?

38
00:02:09,367 --> 00:02:10,333
Oh, no!

39
00:02:10,467 --> 00:02:11,500
Dad?

40
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,333
My child...

41
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,667
I just want to thank you.

42
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:30,233
Thank you for believing in me
and for loving me

43
00:02:30,367 --> 00:02:31,933
as if I were your real father.

44
00:02:33,567 --> 00:02:34,800
You're my father.

45
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:45,167
Why do you look sad?

46
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,500
Is it because of mom?

47
00:02:49,900 --> 00:02:50,933
Yeah.

48
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:55,700
But also,
I'm so worried about you.

49
00:02:55,833 --> 00:02:57,700
Ash, you don't have
to worry about me.

50
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:01,100
Your Uncle Paolo is handling
the security.

51
00:03:02,267 --> 00:03:03,600
So, I'm very safe.

52
00:03:04,967 --> 00:03:06,433
The two of us.

53
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:09,500
It's not just that, Dad.

54
00:03:09,633 --> 00:03:12,400
I just feel hurt knowing
that you might have

55
00:03:12,533 --> 00:03:15,000
to take care of me for life.

56
00:03:18,867 --> 00:03:20,333
My child, that's okay with me.

57
00:03:23,033 --> 00:03:24,200
I'm okay with that.

58
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:28,933
And we'll be okay
even without your mom.

59
00:03:32,467 --> 00:03:33,667
Ashley, my child...

60
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:40,767
I just want you to know that
dad loves you very, very much.

61
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:47,200
Even if my arms get tired
and my hands ache...

62
00:03:48,233 --> 00:03:49,733
even if my back hurts...

63
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:55,467
I will never get tired
of dancing with you

64
00:03:55,633 --> 00:03:57,000
and carrying you...

65
00:03:59,033 --> 00:04:00,467
whenever you want.

66
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,467
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

67
00:04:09,067 --> 00:04:10,733
You're being so dramatic, Dad.

68
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:16,800
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

69
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:23,800
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

70
00:04:27,867 --> 00:04:28,967
I'm here.

71
00:04:30,367 --> 00:04:31,367
Where are you?

72
00:04:38,967 --> 00:04:40,933
Your biggest mistake?

73
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,100
So that's all I ever was
to you, Edward.

74
00:04:47,167 --> 00:04:49,600
I didn't know that you hated me
that much.

75
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:55,267
Between the two of us,

76
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,733
I thought I was the liar.

77
00:04:57,867 --> 00:04:59,367
I was the deceiver.

78
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:02,667
But it turns out,

79
00:05:02,833 --> 00:05:05,400
you were the first one
who betrayed me.

80
00:05:05,533 --> 00:05:08,033
Because from the very beginning,

81
00:05:08,167 --> 00:05:10,233
it was always Marj you wanted!

82
00:05:15,267 --> 00:05:17,067
You're wondering how I know?

83
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,667
To be honest...

84
00:05:22,567 --> 00:05:25,000
I've suspected it
for a long time.

85
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:28,000
But when I heard it earlier
from your own mouth...

86
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:30,600
<i>Because I was so desperate
to erase you, Marj.</i>

87
00:05:30,733 --> 00:05:32,033
<i> I thought back then</i>

88
00:05:32,167 --> 00:05:34,533
<i>that if I had another woman
beside me in bed,</i>

89
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:37,100
<i>I could erase
your image from my mind.</i>

90
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:39,700
<i>I used her to run away
from the truth,</i>

91
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:41,700
<i>but the truth can't be escaped.</i>

92
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:47,300
<i>Thea, she was the biggest
mistake I made in my life.</i>

93
00:05:47,433 --> 00:05:49,333
It felt like I was slapped.

94
00:05:49,467 --> 00:05:53,100
Like I was stabbed
over and over again!

95
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:54,800
What are you even
complaining about?

96
00:05:54,933 --> 00:05:57,233
Haven't you already moved on
with someone else?

97
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:59,600
So why does it matter whether
I loved you before or not?

98
00:05:59,733 --> 00:06:01,667
You have a lot of nerve, Edward!

99
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:06,933
You think you're the only one
who wasted many years?

100
00:06:08,633 --> 00:06:11,667
My whole life as your spouse,

101
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,333
I endured you.

102
00:06:14,433 --> 00:06:15,833
I didn't leave you

103
00:06:15,967 --> 00:06:19,367
even when all you brought
into our life were failures.

104
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:22,567
And then I find out
I was just your replacement?

105
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,267
That's why I broke up with you.

106
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:28,267
So you'd be free
to do whatever you want.

107
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:30,300
So you'd be free from me.

108
00:06:30,433 --> 00:06:32,967
From the person
you've always resented.

109
00:06:35,567 --> 00:06:36,567
You know what?

110
00:06:38,933 --> 00:06:43,633
You know what? I came here
because I still had some love

111
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:46,100
and respect left for you.

112
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:50,767
I was still concerned about you.

113
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:56,400
I needed to warn you
that someone wanted to harm you.

114
00:06:57,867 --> 00:07:02,733
And then I find out all along,
you were disgusted by me.

115
00:07:02,867 --> 00:07:04,500
And to make it worse,

116
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:07,300
it's because you're still
obsessed with Marj!

117
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:10,667
[SOBBING]

118
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,567
You know what?

119
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:14,100
I would have understood it more

120
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:17,067
if you had just cheated on me
with another woman.

121
00:07:18,133 --> 00:07:19,333
At least we'd be even.

122
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:21,967
But Marj?

123
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:25,333
Still Marj?

124
00:07:25,467 --> 00:07:28,300
Even though you know
you'll never have her!

125
00:07:29,767 --> 00:07:32,633
And I was just someone
you settled for?

126
00:07:32,767 --> 00:07:34,933
We're actually the same.

127
00:07:35,067 --> 00:07:37,600
You're furious with me
but you wouldn't leave me.

128
00:07:37,733 --> 00:07:38,767
Why?

129
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:41,000
Because you didn't want to lose

130
00:07:41,133 --> 00:07:43,200
the Torrecampo name
attached to you.

131
00:07:44,933 --> 00:07:49,400
And now, you're pretending
to be concerned about me?

132
00:07:49,567 --> 00:07:51,100
Why?

133
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:53,867
Because you want to get back
into our family?

134
00:07:57,533 --> 00:07:58,700
Where are you, Edward?

135
00:07:59,833 --> 00:08:01,700
Ashley, excuse me.

136
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:03,167
Have you seen your dad?

137
00:08:04,133 --> 00:08:05,033
No, Auntie.

138
00:08:05,167 --> 00:08:07,200
We were just dancing earlier.

139
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:08,967
After that,
I couldn't find him anymore.

140
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,133
I didn't see him too, Mommy.

141
00:08:13,267 --> 00:08:15,167
I thought I heard him
get a phone call.

142
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:16,433
He seemed kind of upset.

143
00:08:19,567 --> 00:08:22,733
If there's someone to blame
for why our marriage failed...

144
00:08:23,933 --> 00:08:25,667
It's you, Thea.

145
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:29,767
Fine! All right!

146
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:32,100
I'm the worthless spouse!

147
00:08:32,233 --> 00:08:34,067
I'm the one
with the bad attitude!

148
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:36,867
There's only one person
who's good enough for you,

149
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,300
right?

150
00:08:38,433 --> 00:08:40,000
That damn Marj?

151
00:08:40,133 --> 00:08:42,100
Yes! You're right!

152
00:08:43,667 --> 00:08:46,567
You're not even close to Marj.

153
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:50,067
And you will never be like her.

154
00:08:53,367 --> 00:08:58,633
And now, you're blaming me
that I'm the failure,

155
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:01,267
that I'm useless and a loser?

156
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,633
Look at you.

157
00:09:03,700 --> 00:09:04,800
Look at yourself.

158
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:06,667
Your life has completely
fallen apart.

159
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,167
You know why?

160
00:09:09,467 --> 00:09:11,800
Because you're
a terrible person.

161
00:09:12,967 --> 00:09:14,867
You're selfish!

162
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,167
You're nothing like Marj

163
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:19,700
who can literally sacrifice
her life for others.

164
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:20,933
So, Thea...

165
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:25,633
don't expect that I'll ever
get back together with you.

166
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:31,367
Because leaving you
was the best decision

167
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:34,800
that I've made in my whole life!

168
00:09:37,033 --> 00:09:39,633
[SOBBING]

169
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:45,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

170
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:46,833
[GRUMBLES]

171
00:09:52,433 --> 00:09:53,467
[THUDS]

172
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:57,333
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

173
00:09:57,467 --> 00:09:58,533
Where is Edward?

174
00:09:58,667 --> 00:09:59,600
Excuse me! Excuse me!

175
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:01,500
Have you seen your Sir Edward?

176
00:10:03,733 --> 00:10:05,600
All right, thank you.

177
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:07,267
[PHONE RINGING]

178
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,633
Hello, Edward?

179
00:10:10,633 --> 00:10:11,767
Edward.

180
00:10:12,967 --> 00:10:15,633
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:19,067
Edward!

182
00:10:21,233 --> 00:10:22,433
Edward!

183
00:10:22,567 --> 00:10:24,600
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:10:27,567 --> 00:10:31,233
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

185
00:10:32,100 --> 00:10:34,167
<i>- Marj.
- Edward?</i>

186
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,733
<i> Help me, Marj.</i>

187
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:40,300
Edward!

188
00:10:42,033 --> 00:10:43,067
Edward!

189
00:10:45,433 --> 00:10:48,067
Edward.
[SOBBING]

190
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,067
Edward.

191
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:51,567
[SOBBING]

192
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:53,833
Edward. Edward.

193
00:10:55,467 --> 00:10:57,200
Edward.

194
00:10:57,333 --> 00:11:00,400
Help, Marj!

195
00:11:00,533 --> 00:11:01,600
Marj?

196
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:05,400
Still Marj?

197
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,467
Help.

198
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,233
Help?

199
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:15,367
Why?

200
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:18,467
You said I was selfish,
didn't you?

201
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:21,200
Fine, I'll own it!

202
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:24,067
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

203
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,267
Marj?

204
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,500
Fine!

205
00:11:26,633 --> 00:11:29,033
Where's the Marj
you're so proud of?

206
00:11:29,167 --> 00:11:30,100
She's not here, is she?

207
00:11:30,233 --> 00:11:31,700
She's not here at all!

208
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:34,600
Thea...

209
00:11:36,067 --> 00:11:37,933
have mercy on me.

210
00:11:38,067 --> 00:11:39,833
Mercy?

211
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,533
Did you have mercy

212
00:11:42,667 --> 00:11:46,633
when you threw me out
of the mansion?

213
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:54,667
Did you have mercy
when you denied me my child?!

214
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,833
Please.

215
00:11:57,967 --> 00:11:59,233
Please, Thea.

216
00:11:59,367 --> 00:12:00,300
Please.

217
00:12:00,433 --> 00:12:04,167
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

218
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,467
Help me, please.

219
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,733
Please?

220
00:12:06,867 --> 00:12:08,733
Stop begging me!

221
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:15,267
You think
I'm your worst mistake?

222
00:12:16,700 --> 00:12:17,733
What about you?

223
00:12:19,100 --> 00:12:23,367
You're the reason for all
the misfortune in my life!

224
00:12:25,467 --> 00:12:26,833
I hate you!

225
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:31,567
Die already!

226
00:12:33,133 --> 00:12:35,333
Paolo!
Paolo, Edward is in danger!

227
00:12:35,467 --> 00:12:38,233
- What?
- What?

228
00:12:38,367 --> 00:12:41,100
<i> Die already, you animal!</i>

229
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:42,700
<i> Aldrin was right.</i>

230
00:12:42,833 --> 00:12:45,667
<i>I should have gotten rid of you
sooner.</i>

231
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,333
Is that Thea?

232
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:48,700
Where are they?

233
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:51,800
I don't know, Dad, but I feel
they're somewhere in this hotel.

234
00:12:51,933 --> 00:12:54,067
Mom, what's going on?

235
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,133
I don't know.

236
00:12:55,267 --> 00:12:56,667
My child, stay here
with your grandfather.

237
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:58,433
Jobert, stay here.

238
00:12:58,567 --> 00:12:59,600
Come on, Marj.

239
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:02,033
- Edward!
- Edward!

240
00:13:02,167 --> 00:13:03,267
Edward, my child!

241
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:06,500
Mom, Paolo, it's better
if we split up.

242
00:13:06,633 --> 00:13:08,433
- What?
- Are you sure?

243
00:13:08,567 --> 00:13:09,900
Yes, I'll be okay.

244
00:13:11,067 --> 00:13:12,867
All right.
You go that way.

245
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,033
Mom, check the other garden.

246
00:13:14,167 --> 00:13:15,667
- I'll head back there, okay?
- Okay.

247
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,333
Okay.

248
00:13:17,467 --> 00:13:19,933
- Edward!
- Love, be careful.

249
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:21,633
If anything happens,
call me right away.

250
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,400
Yes, I promise.

251
00:13:23,533 --> 00:13:24,600
- Okay.
- Take care.

252
00:13:26,967 --> 00:13:28,700
Edward!

253
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:30,567
Edward!

254
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:31,800
Edward?

255
00:13:35,267 --> 00:13:37,000
Edward! Edward!

256
00:13:38,367 --> 00:13:39,467
Edward!

257
00:13:40,767 --> 00:13:41,733
Edward!

258
00:13:43,567 --> 00:13:44,667
Help!

259
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:47,967
Edward!

260
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,667
Edward! Help us!

261
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,400
Help!

262
00:13:52,733 --> 00:13:54,933
Paolo! Mom!

263
00:13:56,133 --> 00:13:57,533
- Edward?
- Mom!

264
00:13:57,667 --> 00:13:58,867
Edward!

265
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,700
[WAILING]

266
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:01,833
Edward!

267
00:14:01,967 --> 00:14:04,100
- What happened? Edward!
- Edward, my child!

268
00:14:04,233 --> 00:14:05,467
Edward!

269
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:06,567
Edward!

270
00:14:08,433 --> 00:14:11,267
- Edward!
- [SOBBING]

271
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,300
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

272
00:14:12,433 --> 00:14:13,533
Lift him, hurry!

273
00:14:13,667 --> 00:14:15,833
Be careful with his neck!

274
00:14:15,967 --> 00:14:17,633
Thea did this!

275
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:19,733
Find that woman!

276
00:14:19,867 --> 00:14:22,133
Don't let her leave this hotel!

277
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:26,267
I'll lock down all exits.

278
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,600
We need to locate Thea.

279
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:29,000
She must not get away!

280
00:14:29,167 --> 00:14:30,267
I'll handle it, Dad!

281
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:33,600
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

282
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:41,933
[CAR KEY ALARMS]

283
00:14:42,067 --> 00:14:43,400
Vien! Vien!

284
00:14:43,533 --> 00:14:44,667
Let's go!

285
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,667
Right now! Hurry!

286
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:47,867
Is that blood, Thea?

287
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,833
I'll explain it later.

288
00:14:49,967 --> 00:14:52,700
Please, don't drag me into
whatever you did!

289
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:53,867
You're on your own!

290
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,000
Vien, wait!

291
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:58,433
Vien, take me with you!

292
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,467
Vien!

293
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,133
Vien, help me, please!

294
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:03,567
Take me with you, Vien!

295
00:15:07,167 --> 00:15:08,400
Vien!

296
00:15:08,533 --> 00:15:10,900
[SOBBING]

297
00:15:13,167 --> 00:15:14,233
Edward.

298
00:15:14,367 --> 00:15:15,800
Edward, stay with us, please!

299
00:15:15,933 --> 00:15:17,467
We're going to the hospital!
Edward, please!

300
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,433
We're close to the hospital!

301
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:21,467
Edward! Edward!

302
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:25,333
Edward, please wake up!

303
00:15:25,467 --> 00:15:26,767
Please, don't leave us!

304
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:29,167
Think of Ashley, Edward!

305
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:31,700
Oscar! Hurry!

306
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,267
To the nearest hospital!

307
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,267
Hurry!

308
00:15:35,433 --> 00:15:36,900
Yes, Ma'am!

309
00:15:37,033 --> 00:15:38,767
[REGINA SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

310
00:15:38,900 --> 00:15:41,800
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

311
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:47,767
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

312
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:59,000
[EXCLAIMS]

313
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:02,767
Thea, get in!

314
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:05,633
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

315
00:16:09,233 --> 00:16:10,500
Thea!

316
00:16:10,633 --> 00:16:15,267
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

317
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,400
Hey!

318
00:16:18,133 --> 00:16:21,400
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

319
00:16:23,467 --> 00:16:25,400
- Mom. Dad.
- What now? What happened?

320
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:26,567
Have you found Thea?

321
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:29,533
- Mom.
- What?

322
00:16:29,667 --> 00:16:31,633
I'm sorry, I tried my best
to catch her,

323
00:16:31,767 --> 00:16:33,833
but someone helped her
so she managed to escape.

324
00:16:35,533 --> 00:16:37,033
Have you identified
who helped her?

325
00:16:37,167 --> 00:16:39,067
Sir, based on the description
of the vehicle

326
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,667
and its plate number,

327
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,667
we have reason to believe
that Aldrin Castelo

328
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:44,100
helped the suspect escape.

329
00:16:46,467 --> 00:16:49,100
Our personnel found the man
who attempted to kill Edward

330
00:16:49,233 --> 00:16:50,967
at the construction site.

331
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:52,500
He was badly beaten,
almost dead,

332
00:16:52,633 --> 00:16:53,933
but they managed to revive him.

333
00:16:54,067 --> 00:16:56,500
And the one identified
as the mastermind is Aldrin.

334
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:59,233
They are absolutely shameless.

335
00:16:59,367 --> 00:17:00,667
Our child is so kind.

336
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:01,867
He doesn't deserve this.

337
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,567
Why is he being targeted?

338
00:17:03,700 --> 00:17:06,233
He didn't do anything wrong!

339
00:17:11,467 --> 00:17:13,867
Doctor, how is Edward?

340
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,133
Doctor, how is my son?

341
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:16,600
Please tell me he's fine.

342
00:17:16,733 --> 00:17:19,967
We've done everything we could
to stabilize him.

343
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:22,633
We've managed to control
the internal bleeding.

344
00:17:22,767 --> 00:17:24,467
But he sustained
severe injuries

345
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,967
and lost a significant
amount of blood.

346
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:30,400
So, can we see him now?

347
00:17:30,533 --> 00:17:32,300
I'll be honest with you.

348
00:17:32,433 --> 00:17:36,233
His body is under
extreme trauma.

349
00:17:36,367 --> 00:17:40,000
At any moment,
his body could give out.

350
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:43,100
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

351
00:17:43,233 --> 00:17:46,533
No. No. No.

352
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:50,367
No. No.
[SOBBING]

353
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,967
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

354
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:01,367
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

355
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,867
<i>Authorities are searching
for Thea Torrecampo</i>

356
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,167
<i> and Aldrin Castelo</i>

357
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:13,467
<i>in connection with separate
attempted murders</i>

358
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,433
<i> against Edward Torrecampo,</i>

359
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:18,967
<i>a member of the family
that owns Torrecampo Realty.</i>

360
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:21,533
<i>The manhunt continues
for the two suspects.</i>

361
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:24,300
<i>The victim's family
has also offered a reward</i>

362
00:18:24,433 --> 00:18:27,000
<i>for the immediate arrest
of the accused.</i>

363
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,200
Attempted murder?

364
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:37,333
Edward is still alive!

365
00:18:39,267 --> 00:18:41,300
My child.

366
00:18:41,433 --> 00:18:44,500
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:53,400
If you're already tired...

368
00:18:56,133 --> 00:18:58,767
if you're already in pain...

369
00:19:02,067 --> 00:19:04,467
you can rest now.

370
00:19:09,867 --> 00:19:13,867
I can't bear to see you
suffering like this.

371
00:19:17,133 --> 00:19:21,600
My sweet, sweet, brave boy.

372
00:19:28,533 --> 00:19:31,367
I love you so much.

373
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:34,167
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

374
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,900
You can let go of all the pain.

375
00:19:42,433 --> 00:19:44,700
Mom will be okay.

376
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:48,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

377
00:20:03,067 --> 00:20:04,933
Who cares about Edward?

378
00:20:05,067 --> 00:20:06,667
Didn't you hear?

379
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:07,867
We're wanted now.

380
00:20:09,167 --> 00:20:10,533
I need to go to him
at the hospital.

381
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:12,300
I'll explain everything to him.

382
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:14,167
I'll apologize to mom.

383
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:16,067
Maybe they'll listen to me.

384
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:18,400
I'm not a criminal.

385
00:20:18,533 --> 00:20:19,600
No, no, no.

386
00:20:19,733 --> 00:20:21,033
- No, you're not.
- Please.

387
00:20:21,167 --> 00:20:23,267
You're not going anywhere, Thea.

388
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:25,233
You're not going anywhere.

389
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:27,533
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

390
00:20:28,567 --> 00:20:29,667
No!

391
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:31,433
I can't become wanted.

392
00:20:31,567 --> 00:20:33,300
I don't want to go to jail!

393
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:37,200
I'll just apologize to them
so everything can be fixed.

394
00:20:37,367 --> 00:20:38,600
Wake up already!

395
00:20:38,867 --> 00:20:40,467
Look at the goddamn news!

396
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:42,200
We're wanted!

397
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:44,633
We're criminals
in the eyes of the public!

398
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:50,067
And do you honestly think
the Torrecampos will forgive you

399
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,533
after you tried to kill Edward?

400
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:54,000
Think about it!

401
00:20:55,167 --> 00:21:00,167
What they want to see
is for you to rot in jail.

402
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:02,667
I'm the only one you have left.

403
00:21:03,767 --> 00:21:07,833
We have no one else to rely on
except each other.

404
00:21:12,633 --> 00:21:17,900
I thought we still had
plenty of time.

405
00:21:18,033 --> 00:21:21,867
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

406
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,500
I thought...

407
00:21:27,267 --> 00:21:29,567
there was still time
to make things right.

408
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,933
I was wrong.

409
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:38,433
I was so wrong.

410
00:21:38,567 --> 00:21:41,500
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

411
00:21:43,900 --> 00:21:46,233
[SOBBING]

412
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:52,100
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

413
00:21:56,867 --> 00:21:59,367
[SOBBING]

414
00:22:02,533 --> 00:22:04,433
Aldrin, please,
get me out of here.

415
00:22:04,567 --> 00:22:05,633
Take me far away from here.

416
00:22:05,767 --> 00:22:08,333
Let's just leave everything
behind. Please.

417
00:22:08,467 --> 00:22:12,067
Yes. We're leaving, okay?

418
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:14,300
I've already had an escape plan.

419
00:22:14,433 --> 00:22:16,133
But before we leave...

420
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:19,633
there's still something
I need to finish.

421
00:22:20,667 --> 00:22:23,367
One final act.

422
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:24,833
What is it?

423
00:22:28,167 --> 00:22:30,333
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

424
00:22:30,467 --> 00:22:31,700
Regina.

425
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:36,867
As long as that woman
is still breathing...

426
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:40,067
I won't have peace.

427
00:22:41,833 --> 00:22:44,467
To complete my revenge
against her...

428
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:47,767
I will finish her.

429
00:22:49,700 --> 00:22:52,300
I will kill Regina Torrecampo.

430
00:22:52,433 --> 00:22:56,200
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

431
00:23:05,333 --> 00:23:06,867
Forgive me...

432
00:23:08,367 --> 00:23:12,500
for all the wrongs I've done,
Bro.

433
00:23:12,633 --> 00:23:13,933
Edward.

434
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:17,200
I took you for granted.

435
00:23:18,467 --> 00:23:23,667
I should have been
a better brother...

436
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:26,433
and supported you

437
00:23:26,567 --> 00:23:28,400
during the times...

438
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:32,600
when you needed me the most.

439
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,767
And believe me,

440
00:23:37,133 --> 00:23:40,900
if only I can turn back time...

441
00:23:41,733 --> 00:23:44,000
I wouldn't hesitate,

442
00:23:44,933 --> 00:23:46,700
I would do it.

443
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:49,333
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

444
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:00,100
Edward.

445
00:24:02,133 --> 00:24:04,267
Don't worry about Ashley.

446
00:24:06,067 --> 00:24:08,100
We'll take care of her.

447
00:24:09,300 --> 00:24:11,100
We'll love her.

448
00:24:14,133 --> 00:24:17,567
Just like how you loved her.

449
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:19,667
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

450
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:22,233
[SOBBING]

451
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:28,867
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

452
00:24:29,933 --> 00:24:33,533
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

453
00:24:38,967 --> 00:24:42,100
[FLATLINE TONE]

454
00:24:43,433 --> 00:24:44,667
[SOBBING]

455
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:45,900
- Doctor!
- Edward.

456
00:24:46,033 --> 00:24:48,033
Nurse! Doctor! Help!

457
00:24:48,167 --> 00:24:49,300
Edward...

458
00:24:49,433 --> 00:24:51,300
Code blue!
Clear the room, please.

459
00:24:51,433 --> 00:24:52,100
Clear the room.

460
00:24:52,233 --> 00:24:54,767
[REGINA SOBBING]

461
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:56,867
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

462
00:24:59,033 --> 00:25:02,300
No! No! No!

463
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:07,900
[REGINA SOBBING]

464
00:25:08,033 --> 00:25:11,200
[FLATLINE TONE CONTINUES]

465
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:14,067
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

466
00:25:18,367 --> 00:25:21,200
- Time of death, 2:43 A.M.
- No! No!

467
00:25:21,333 --> 00:25:24,533
No! No!
[WAILING]

468
00:25:24,667 --> 00:25:26,600
No!

469
00:25:26,733 --> 00:25:30,733
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

470
00:25:30,867 --> 00:25:34,467
[SOBBING]

471
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:37,833
No! No! No!

472
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,500
No! No!

473
00:25:39,633 --> 00:25:46,233
No! No!
[WAILING]

474
00:25:46,367 --> 00:25:48,200
Not my son!

475
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:54,300
[SOBBING]

476
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:05,133
Jasmine, all my life,
dad was the one on my side.

477
00:26:05,267 --> 00:26:08,700
Every time I felt pressured
by mom about school,

478
00:26:08,867 --> 00:26:12,733
he would tell me that no matter
what my grades were, it's okay.

479
00:26:12,867 --> 00:26:17,433
I wasn't even given a chance
to make things right.

480
00:26:18,700 --> 00:26:21,333
Mom has a charity event
in memory of Edward.

481
00:26:21,467 --> 00:26:23,500
I think it's the perfect time
to strike.

482
00:26:23,633 --> 00:26:24,700
This is great.

483
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:27,267
I think I found my opportunity.

484
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:28,567
I've been knocking

485
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:30,400
on mom and grandmother's door
for a while now

486
00:26:30,533 --> 00:26:31,733
because mom has my medicine,

487
00:26:31,867 --> 00:26:34,333
but it seems like
they're not inside.

488
00:26:34,467 --> 00:26:36,033
I'm the only one you need.

489
00:26:36,167 --> 00:26:37,267
Let Marj go.

490
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:39,367
Please don't involve her.

491
00:26:39,500 --> 00:26:43,033
Don't waste your strength
begging!

492
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:44,533
[GUN FIRES]
